workflow.description:
# üì¨ What this workflow does
Every morning ‚Üí fetch 3 French economy RSS feeds ‚Üí keep fresh items ‚Üí AI rewrites into short summaries ‚Üí send a nice HTML email newsletter.

---

# üîÑ Flow (high level)
1. ‚è∞ Trigger at 07:00  
2. üì∞ Fetch RSS (Le Monde, Usine Nouvelle, Le Figaro)  
3. ‚õî Filter ‚Üí keep only recent items  
4. üî¢ Sort newest first  
5. ‚úÇÔ∏è Limit 2 per source  
6. ‚ûï Merge  
7. ü§ñ AI summary (title + paragraph)  
8. üè∑ Normalize fields (title, source, link‚Ä¶)  
9. üì¶ Aggregate arrays  
10. üìß Send via Outlook (HTML template)

---

# üß© Node notes
- **Trigger** ‚Üí 07:00 daily (check timezone).  
- **RSS Read** ‚Üí feeds OK, but UsineNouvelle is `http` (redirects fine).  
- **If** nodes ‚Üí ‚ùó currently `after $today` ‚Üí keeps only future dates.  
  - Fix:  
    - For *today only*: `after $today.startOf('day')`  
    - For *last 24h*: `after $now.minus({ hours: 24 })`  
- **Sort + Limit** ‚Üí newest 2 per feed.  
- **Merge** ‚Üí combine up to 6 items.  
- **AI agent** ‚Üí prompt uses `<article>` ‚Ä¶ needs closing `</article>` ‚úÖ  
- **Edit Fields** ‚Üí maps source domains ‚Üí nice labels (‚ÄúLe Monde‚Äù etc).  
- **Aggregate** ‚Üí arrays for email template.  
- **Outlook email** ‚Üí HTML newsletter (mobile-friendly).

---

# ‚ö° Quick wins
- üïí Fix the **date filter** logic (today/24h).  
- üìù Fix **closing tag** in AI prompt (`</article>`).  
- üåç Add **User-Agent** header in RSS nodes (avoid 403).  
- üîÅ Remove duplicates on `link`.  
- ‚è≥ Mind the server **timezone** vs your audience.  

---

data.details:
The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.
